name: Digital Harbor
overview: Digital Harbor, Inc. provides risk management and compliance solutions for the financial services, industry, and public sector clients. It develops and markets PiiE, a platform for composite applications, which provides information integration solution and information management system for enterprises. The companyâ€™s products include Smart Client, a composite application interface layer that provides a standards-based method for delivering Internet applications; and Fusion Server, a composite application engine that manages integrated set of services for information integration and management. It offers solutions for anti-money laundering, fraud, knowing customer, enterprise case management, and risk management to the financial services industry; and solutions for insider threat, command and control, incident management, mission management, analyst workbench, logistics, and network centric operations to the federal government, intelligence community, homeland security, and public work organizations. Digital Harbor also provides support, implementation, and training services. In addition, it has a strategic alliance with eFunds Corporation to deliver fraud investigation solutions to the banking industry. Digital Harbor, Inc. was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Reston, Virginia. As of July 31, 2007, Digital Harbor, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Norkom Group Plc (ISE:N5OK).

funding_rounds.source_description: Article: Digital Harbor Secures $11 Million in Series B Financing; Financing From FTVentures and Insight Venture Partners Caps Year of 100 Percent Growth for Company.
